SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 128
BY SENATOR KLEINPETER
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and honors the 40th Anniversary of Entergy's River Bend
Station in St. Francisville.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and honor the 40th anniversary of Entergy's River Bend Station located in St.
3 Francisville, Louisiana, and recognizing the important role nuclear power plays in
4 providing safe and reliable electricity to Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, Entergy's River Bend Station has proudly served the residents of West
6 Feliciana Parish, the state of Louisiana, and the Gulf Coast region for 40 years, providing
7 safe, reliable, and carbon-free electricity since commencing commercial operation in 1986;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, River Bend Station is a cornerstone of energy resilience in Southeast
10 Louisiana, playing a vital role in meeting the power needs of nearly half a million customers
11 by providing a maximum dependable capacity of 978 megawatts and contributing to grid
12 stability during periods of peak demand and extreme weather events; and
13 WHEREAS, River Bend Station employs more than 800 employees and contractors
14 who have demonstrated a commitment to operational excellence, nuclear safety, emergency
15 preparedness and professional standards, exemplifying the spirit of public service and
16 technical leadership; and
17 WHEREAS, River Bend Station has maintained a strong and ongoing partnership
18 with the West Feliciana, East Feliciana, Pointe Coupee, and East Baton Rouge community,
